  abstract: "Quasi-periodic eruptions (QPEs) from supermassive black holes represent a new window for testing the properties of accretion physics and black hole spacetime geometry. We investigate the detectability of gravitational waves produced during quasi-periodic eruptions in the source RX J1301.9+2747 with the Laser Interferometer Space Antenna (LISA). We model the dynamics of the accretion disk and compute the expected gravitational wave strain from the orbital evolution of the orbiting bodies during QPE cycles. Our results show that LISA should be capable of detecting gravitational wave signals from nearby QPE sources, opening new possibilities for multi-messenger observations of AGN."

- id: yang2026_wd_imbh
  title: "Relativistic Tidal Dissipation and the Gravitational-Wave Signal of a White Dwarf Orbiting an Intermediate-Mass Black Hole"
  authors:
    - name: "Y. Yang"
      isHighlighted: false
    - name: "L. Lui"
      isHighlighted: true
    - name: "A. Torres-Orjuela"
