    - name: "X. Chen"
      isHighlighted: false
  year: 2026
  month: 3
  journal: "The Astrophysical Journal"
  volume: "XXX"
  issue: "XXX"
  pages: "XXX"
  doi: "10.48550/arXiv.2601.xxxxx"
  url: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.xxxxx"
  preview: "wd-imbh.png"
  selected: false
  abstract: "White dwarfs orbiting intermediate-mass black holes (IMBHs) represent a new class of compact binary systems accessible to space-based gravitational wave detectors. We analyze the relativistic effects of tidal dissipation in such systems and compute the expected gravitational wave signatures for LISA and other future detectors. We model the tidal deformation of the white dwarf and derive the rate of energy dissipation as a function of orbital parameters. Our calculations show that these systems can produce detectable gravitational wave signals over observation timescales, providing constraints on IMBH demographics."
